From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 09:52:46 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] kati: VPATH directory search + pattern-rule remade includes
 (kernel build)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The kernel build in a -b box, past the sub-make fix, died at
`make -f $(srctree)/scripts/Makefile.build obj=scripts/basic`:

    *** No rule to make target 'scripts/basic/fixdep.c', needed by
        'scripts/basic/fixdep'.

Out-of-tree kbuild resolves every source prerequisite through GNU
make's VPATH directory search (`VPATH := $(srctree)`), which kati
did not implement at all. And one step later the build's required
`include include/config/auto.conf` is regenerated by a PATTERN rule
(`%/auto.conf %/auto.conf.cmd: $(KCONFIG_CONFIG)` → syncconfig),
which the remake-the-makefile loop rejected — it only accepted rules
whose literal outputs named the missing include.

- dep.rs: DepBuilder now snapshots $(VPATH)'s final value (split on
  ':'/whitespace, as GNU does) and rewrites relative prerequisites that
  have no rule, aren't phony, and don't exist in the working dir to
  their first VPATH hit — before recursing, and reflected into
  actual_inputs so $^/$< and the executor's mtime checks see the
  found path. A VPATH hit also counts as "existing" for implicit-rule
  selection.

- katirun.rs / main.rs: the pending-remake-include check accepts a
  producer whose output_patterns match the missing file, not just
  literal outputs.

Verified against a real linux v5.6 tree built from its parent
directory (srctree != objtree) in a box: `make defconfig` +
`make -j8 scripts` now complete; both failed before (fixdep.c, then
auto.conf). testcase/vpath_directory_search.mk pins GNU parity in the
corpus; test_make_rs case 21 covers both fixes end-to-end in a box.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01B97aMMA3rHQW7gsyBB2Cpa
